com.sun.messaging.bridge.service
Class MessageTransformer<T,S>

java.lang.Object
  com.sun.messaging.bridge.service.MessageTransformer<T,S>

public abstract class MessageTransformer<T,S>
extends java.lang.Object

The message transformer class to be extended by user. Its implementation must provide a public zero-argument constructor. The following is an example usage of this class 

 import java.util.*;
 import javax.jms.*;
 import com.sun.messaging.bridge.service.MessageTransformer;

 public class MessageTran extends MessageTransformer <Message, Message> {

 public Message transform(Message msg, 
                          boolean readOnly,
                          String charsetName,
                          String source, 
                          String target,
                          Properties props)
                          throws Exception {
    Message m = msg;
    if (source.equals(STOMP)) { //from STOMP client
        if (msg instanceof TextMessage) {
            TextMessage tm = (TextMessage)msg;
            ......
            m = tm;
        }

    } else if (source.equals(SUN_MQ)) { //from Java Message Queue

        //create a new MapMessage for msg to be transformed to 
        MapMessage mm = (MapMessage)createJMSMessage(JMSMessageType.MAPMESSAGE);
        ......
        m = mm;
    }
    return m;
 }

Method Detail

init

public final void init(java.lang.Object obj)
This method is called by the bridge service, e.g. the STOMP server, before transform() is called. A message transformer object is initialized by init() each time before transform() is called. After transform() returns, it's back to uninitialized state.

createJMSMessage

protected final javax.jms.Message createJMSMessage(MessageTransformer.JMSMessageType type)
                                            throws java.lang.Exception
Create a JMS message object. This method is to be used in tranform() method implemenation when it needs to create a new JMS message

Parameters:
type - The type of the JMS message to be created
Returns:
a newly created uninitialized JMS message object
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if this message transformer object is not initialized
JMSException - if fails create the JMS message
java.lang.Exception

To be implemented by user

Parameters:
msg - The message object to be tranformed.
readOnly - if the msg is in read-only mode (For STOMP server, false if source is STOMP; true if source is SUN_MQ)
charsetName - The charset name of msg if applicable (e.g. specifies the message body character encoding if msg is a JMS BytesMessage from STOMP client), null if not available
source - The source provider name
target - The target provider name
props - any properties configured for the message transformer, null if none
Returns:
a message object that is transformed from msg
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - if unable to transform msg
